 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">The classical Doppler effect produced by an accelerated source is considered by using a naive kinematical, graphical approach. We obtain expressions for the frecuency detected by a stationary observer from a source that moves towards or away from him. An extension to the relativistic case is also analysed.</subfield>
